        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs. 11–14. Remenus bilobatus, larva, 11. Head and pronotum, A = pale M-shaped mark, B = pale enclosed anterolateral oval spot, C = postocular setae, D = large enclosed posterolateral oval spot, E = long erect marginal setae, ES = epicranial suture, Lb = labrum, Mp = maxillary palp, Th1 = pronotum. 12. Left lacinia, dorsal, A = minute irregularly spaced setae, B = minute submarginal setae, BK = basal knob. 13. Left mandible, dorsal, A = Middle three teeth with proximal margins lightly serrated. 14. Head, ventral, Gl = glossa, La = lacinia, Lb = labrum, LP = labial palp, Ma = mandible, MP = maxillary palp, Pg = paraglossa, PM = prementum." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4757885/files/figure.png" .

