        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs. 7–10. Remenus bilobatus adult and ovum. 7. Male terminalia, lateral, A = posterodorsal lobes, Ae = aedeagus, Ab = abdominal segment, B = lateral lobes, Co = Cowl, DS = dorsal sclerite, Ep = epiproct, HL = hemitergal lobe, PP = paragenital plate. 8. Female abdominal sterna 8–10, Ab = abdominal segment, BC = basolateral crease, SP = subgenital plate. 9. Ovum, dorsal, A = globules, B = diamond-shaped follicle cell impressions, C = collar, D = dorsal keel. 10. Ovum, ventral, A = Collar, B = diamond-shaped follicle cell impressions, C = micropyles." ;
